[Justifiable Defense]

2
00:01:46,030 --> 00:01:48,990
[Episode 9]

3
00:01:49,090 --> 00:01:51,660
[Wuyan Municiple Detention Center]

4
00:02:10,220 --> 00:02:11,150
Open your mouth.

5
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:16,520
Okay.

6
00:02:17,630 --> 00:02:19,760
If you still feel unwell, just report.

7
00:02:20,150 --> 00:02:21,150
Back to your cell.

8
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:40,280
Stand up.

9
00:02:42,190 --> 00:02:43,800
Turn left. Turn right.

10
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:48,280
This is the new inmate, No. 033, Wang Hao.

11
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:50,280
Look out for each other from now on.

12
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:51,800
Duan Hongshan. Qiao Guan.

13
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:52,600
-Here.
-Here.

14
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:55,120
You two are in charge of him from now on.

15
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:55,780
-Yes.
-Yes.

16
00:02:56,470 --> 00:02:57,030
Alright.

17
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:59,240
After lunch, we'll have
a three-point positioning training.

18
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:00,150
Yes.

19
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:02,150
Your spot. Go eat.

20
00:03:11,030 --> 00:03:11,840
Lunch time.

21
00:03:11,930 --> 00:03:20,030
[A fall from the edge
can still be a new beginning]

22
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:22,460
What are you doing?

23
00:03:22,910 --> 00:03:24,310
Don't recognize me?

24
00:03:24,310 --> 00:03:25,970
"Look at me. Look at me. Look."

25
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:29,180
Look here. Look at me.

26
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:31,240
A few days ago, bang bang,
I knocked on the glass.

27
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:32,440
I shot you, remember?

28
00:03:33,190 --> 00:03:34,380
Let me tell you all.

29
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:35,810
He's a prosecutor.

30
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:37,120
He killed someone.

31
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:38,450
-A prosecutor?
-I shot him.

32
00:03:38,450 --> 00:03:39,870
[A fall from the edge
can still be a new beginning]

33
00:03:39,870 --> 00:03:40,790
That's me.

34
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:43,290
The guy knocking on the car window.

35
00:03:45,450 --> 00:03:46,630
[A fall from the edge
can still be a new beginning]

36
00:03:46,630 --> 00:03:47,910
A prosecutor who's killed.

37
00:03:47,910 --> 00:03:49,840
Bet you've never seen this before.

38
00:03:59,710 --> 00:04:01,630
Lingyuan, time to eat.

39
00:04:03,030 --> 00:04:04,080
You come down?

40
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:05,970
We'll eat when your dad's home.

41
00:04:07,150 --> 00:04:08,610
Why did Dad go out so early?

42
00:04:09,190 --> 00:04:10,990
He went to make a delivery again?

43
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:12,750
How many times have I said this?

44
00:04:12,750 --> 00:04:13,910
Hire someone.

45
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:16,339
It's dangerous biking around alone.

46
00:04:16,870 --> 00:04:17,940
If it really doesn't work,

47
00:04:17,940 --> 00:04:20,190
just use a delivery service.

48
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:22,040
They're everywhere.

49
00:04:22,190 --> 00:04:23,950
His customers are regulars.

50
00:04:23,950 --> 00:04:26,000
And they live nearby.

51
00:04:26,830 --> 00:04:28,360
Why make a fuss over it?

52
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:34,720
You're back.

53
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:40,270
Your dad said you looked even thinner.

54
00:04:40,750 --> 00:04:43,190
He biked to the market
just to buy this for you.

55
00:04:43,190 --> 00:04:44,100
Come on.

56
00:04:44,430 --> 00:04:45,240
Try it.

57
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:46,360
Let's eat.

58
00:04:50,510 --> 00:04:51,310
Thanks, Dad.

59
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:01,680
Lingyuan.

60
00:05:02,870 --> 00:05:03,920
About the past...

61
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:04,510
Mom.

62
00:05:06,390 --> 00:05:07,240
I'm okay now.

63
00:05:07,750 --> 00:05:08,390
Really.

64
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:19,270
Dad.

65
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:25,090
I'm sorry.

66
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:30,950
Lingyuan.

67
00:05:31,310 --> 00:05:32,040
Let's eat.

68
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:34,860
I'm not hungry.

69
00:05:40,190 --> 00:05:41,510
Where's your new dress?

70
00:05:41,510 --> 00:05:42,970
Why aren't you wearing it?

71
00:05:46,870 --> 00:05:48,400
Don't feel like it anymore.

72
00:05:59,190 --> 00:06:00,010
I'm sorry.

73
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:14,930
The fish is still alive.

74
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:17,020
As for the case,

75
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:18,820
it's basically clear now.

76
00:06:19,310 --> 00:06:21,600
The evidence from the hearing

77
00:06:22,190 --> 00:06:23,520
also indirectly proves

78
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:26,600
Zhang Yuan likely
had a history of domestic violence.

79
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:27,510
That would make

80
00:06:28,190 --> 00:06:29,310
Jiang Ting's case

81
00:06:29,750 --> 00:06:31,270
a likely act

82
00:06:31,510 --> 00:06:32,909
of justifiable defense.

83
00:06:34,190 --> 00:06:36,630
It means Zhou Delong's accusation
against Duan Hongshan

84
00:06:36,630 --> 00:06:37,680
doesn't hold up.

85
00:06:38,159 --> 00:06:39,430
It also confirms

86
00:06:40,159 --> 00:06:42,720
Duan Hongshan didn't mishandle

87
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:44,680
the case 14 years ago.

88
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:46,250
What a coincidence.

89
00:06:48,430 --> 00:06:49,310
Coincidence?

90
00:06:50,300 --> 00:06:51,830
You mean Duan Hongshan?

91
00:06:52,430 --> 00:06:53,750
It all seems

92
00:06:53,750 --> 00:06:55,550
unrelated to him on the surface,

93
00:06:56,430 --> 00:06:58,510
but each step somehow proves

94
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,450
he never made a mistake.

95
00:07:02,270 --> 00:07:05,270
Don't you think it's coincidental,
Prosecutor Gong?

96
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:11,600
From Jiang Ting's case to the hearing...

97
00:07:12,510 --> 00:07:13,190
What?

98
00:07:14,120 --> 00:07:16,630
Are you doubting your own investigation?

99
00:07:16,630 --> 00:07:17,310
No.

100
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:19,140
I'm just wondering

101
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:23,510
whether I really see the whole truth.

102
00:07:24,550 --> 00:07:26,160
When you first got here,

103
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:28,490
you never questioned yourself like this.

104
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:30,390
People change.

105
00:07:35,310 --> 00:07:37,270
Why didn't you ever tell me

106
00:07:37,390 --> 00:07:39,159
you knew Jiang Ting?

107
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:44,680
Because it doesn't affect my judgment.

108
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:45,800
Maybe not.

109
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:47,680
Maybe it does.

110
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:51,830
You volunteered to take this case.

111
00:07:53,870 --> 00:07:56,070
It was because of Jiang Ting, wasn't it?

112
00:07:58,159 --> 00:07:59,159
Prosecutor Gong.

113
00:07:59,750 --> 00:08:01,280
There are no maybes with me.

114
00:08:04,190 --> 00:08:05,430
Deputy Chief Prosecutor Fang.

115
00:08:05,430 --> 00:08:06,120
What's up?

116
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:08,000
We got Zhou Delong's phone back.

117
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:09,270
And?

118
00:08:09,510 --> 00:08:10,430
It was underwater

119
00:08:10,430 --> 00:08:10,490
too long.

120
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:11,280
[Evidence from the West Suburb
Fishery Murder Case: Cellphone]

121
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:13,090
The motherboard's ruined.

122
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:16,870
Got it. Carry on.

123
00:08:22,260 --> 00:08:24,310
Bro, tell me

124
00:08:24,310 --> 00:08:26,430
what happens
when a cat walks into a den of rats.

125
00:08:26,430 --> 00:08:27,390
Who's the cat?

126
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:29,000
A cat with no claws

127
00:08:29,100 --> 00:08:30,360
or fangs,

128
00:08:30,430 --> 00:08:32,090
can it still call itself a cat?

129
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:35,760
What did he even do?

130
00:08:35,870 --> 00:08:37,530
Don't ask what you shouldn't.

131
00:08:37,669 --> 00:08:39,480
Curiosity killed the cat.

132
00:08:39,630 --> 00:08:41,750
He used to interrogate us every day.

133
00:08:41,870 --> 00:08:42,870
Now we finally get a chance...

134
00:08:42,870 --> 00:08:45,870
-Duan Hongshan.
-Let's interrogate him for a change.

135
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:47,510
Because of prosecutors like you...

136
00:08:47,510 --> 00:08:48,000
Stop him!

137
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,150
My dad died before I could
even see him one last time.

138
00:08:50,150 --> 00:08:53,240
Give my father back. Give him back!

139
00:08:53,790 --> 00:08:55,190
Hands on your head!

140
00:08:55,390 --> 00:08:56,510
Give him back!

141
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:58,360
Give him back!

142
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:00,200
Give him back!

143
00:09:00,750 --> 00:09:02,440
Give him back!

144
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:04,270
Give him back!

145
00:09:04,270 --> 00:09:05,440
Hands on your head!

146
00:09:10,270 --> 00:09:11,080
Qiao Guan.

147
00:09:11,550 --> 00:09:12,390
Stand up.

148
00:09:15,790 --> 00:09:17,450
Why did you hit Duan Hongshan?

149
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:20,630
Sir.

150
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:21,670
I saw it.

151
00:09:21,670 --> 00:09:23,130
Duan Hongshan started it.

152
00:09:29,870 --> 00:09:30,720
Is that true?

153
00:09:30,790 --> 00:09:31,840
-Yes.
-Yes.

154
00:09:41,270 --> 00:09:42,390
Heard you fainted.

155
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:44,410
How are you feeling now?

156
00:09:44,960 --> 00:09:45,870
Still alive.

157
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:48,080
Do you need more time to recover,

158
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:49,870
or can we begin?

159
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:53,360
Let's begin.

160
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,800
Have you seen this phone before?

161
00:10:11,550 --> 00:10:13,030
Everyone saw it, right?

162
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:14,870
This is Duan Hongshan, Director

163
00:10:14,870 --> 00:10:16,170
of the First Procuratorial Department
of Wuyan Procuratorate.

164
00:10:16,170 --> 00:10:17,630
[Live Broadcast]

165
00:10:17,630 --> 00:10:19,200
This is the same phone model

166
00:10:19,270 --> 00:10:21,530
Zhou Delong used to livestream that day.

167
00:10:26,630 --> 00:10:28,490
Were you able to recover any data?

168
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:33,080
I can't tell you that for now.

169
00:10:37,030 --> 00:10:39,030
Because it was underwater too long,

170
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:42,160
the data couldn't be recovered?

171
00:10:44,270 --> 00:10:45,480
Even so,

172
00:10:45,910 --> 00:10:47,120
that doesn't prove

173
00:10:47,150 --> 00:10:48,680
I tried to kill Zhou Delong.

174
00:10:51,520 --> 00:10:53,310
He was always monitoring me,

175
00:10:53,870 --> 00:10:55,270
even stalking me.

176
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:57,810
He lived just one wall away.

177
00:10:57,950 --> 00:11:00,120
He also filed an anonymous
complaint against me.

178
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:01,510
He questioned my sentencing recommendation

179
00:11:01,510 --> 00:11:03,630
for Case 6.28 14 years ago.

180
00:11:04,270 --> 00:11:05,510
So he had plenty of

181
00:11:05,510 --> 00:11:07,240
motive and reason to harm me.

182
00:11:07,240 --> 00:11:09,630
But Zhou Delong is a 67-year-old man.

183
00:11:20,390 --> 00:11:22,320
Zhou Delong is already 67 years old

184
00:11:22,750 --> 00:11:24,000
And he has cancer.

185
00:11:24,440 --> 00:11:25,640
From my point of view,

186
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:29,000
he posed no threat to your life.

187
00:11:29,020 --> 00:11:30,100
You're wrong.

188
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:31,490
He was premeditated.

189
00:11:31,730 --> 00:11:33,490
He had a detailed plan.

190
00:11:33,670 --> 00:11:35,240
I was ambushed.

191
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:36,870
At that critical moment,

192
00:11:37,150 --> 00:11:39,210
only one thought ran through my mind:

193
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:40,720
I must not die.

194
00:11:41,030 --> 00:11:42,390
Put yourself in the defendant's shoes.

195
00:11:42,390 --> 00:11:43,750
Put yourself in the defendant's shoes.

196
00:11:43,750 --> 00:11:44,550
Imagine

197
00:11:44,550 --> 00:11:46,550
if you were in my place,

198
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:48,240
if he had you pinned down like that,

199
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:49,640
what would you have done?

200
00:11:50,230 --> 00:11:51,420
You know very well

201
00:11:51,870 --> 00:11:54,000
the chain of evidence is still incomplete.

202
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:55,030
And when you're unable

203
00:11:55,030 --> 00:11:56,670
to prove everything,

204
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:58,080
our law dictates

205
00:11:58,080 --> 00:11:59,720
that any doubt must benefit the suspect.

206
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:02,250
Presumed innocence
in cases of uncertainty.

207
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:12,870
Ding Yi.

208
00:12:14,240 --> 00:12:16,240
Pour Duan Hongshan a glass of water.

209
00:12:17,080 --> 00:12:18,210
Ding Yi, take notes.

210
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:34,360
If I weren't a prosecutor,

211
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:38,610
if I were just an ordinary person,

212
00:12:40,720 --> 00:12:42,000
would I already

213
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,480
be released by now?

214
00:12:47,910 --> 00:12:50,700
It's because I'm a prosecutor

215
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:52,440
that you can't rule this

216
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:53,840
as justifiable defense.

217
00:12:54,790 --> 00:12:56,270
Otherwise, the public would accuse

218
00:12:56,270 --> 00:12:58,200
our justice system of protecting its own.

219
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:59,000
Right?

220
00:13:22,850 --> 00:13:23,710
Duan Hongshan.

221
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:28,150
I know who you want to hear those words.

222
00:13:31,020 --> 00:13:32,630
You want others to see

223
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:34,600
that what you're going through

224
00:13:35,010 --> 00:13:37,470
is because of
your identity as a prosecutor.

225
00:13:39,220 --> 00:13:41,580
But the public won't buy it

226
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:44,320
because this case is so unusual.

227
00:13:45,080 --> 00:13:46,810
They simply can't understand.

228
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:06,390
Yingying.

229
00:14:06,750 --> 00:14:07,750
Go home first.

230
00:14:07,830 --> 00:14:09,360
Mom has something

231
00:14:09,360 --> 00:14:10,490
to deal with at work.

232
00:14:13,010 --> 00:14:14,270
Is it about Dad?

233
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:15,730
Yes, it's about Dad.

234
00:14:17,360 --> 00:14:18,240
Dad is sick.

235
00:14:19,790 --> 00:14:21,080
Dad… is sick?

236
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:23,030
Dad is sick,

237
00:14:23,030 --> 00:14:24,240
But trust Mommy.

238
00:14:24,720 --> 00:14:26,600
I'll bring him home

239
00:14:26,870 --> 00:14:28,870
before he's too weak to hold on, okay?

240
00:14:28,870 --> 00:14:31,030
So tonight, can you do
your homework on your own,

241
00:14:31,030 --> 00:14:33,230
eat by yourself, and sleep by yourself?

242
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:36,640
Mommy believes in you. Go ahead.

243
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:39,080
Don't worry.

244
00:15:15,810 --> 00:15:17,070
Director Duan is sick?

245
00:15:19,840 --> 00:15:21,080
If he's sick,

246
00:15:21,550 --> 00:15:23,030
can't he go to a hospital?

247
00:15:24,910 --> 00:15:27,080
There are doctors in the detention center.

248
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:28,120
So he can't leave.

249
00:15:35,630 --> 00:15:37,690
I've lived with Dad for so many years.

250
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:40,870
He rarely gets sick.

251
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:43,100
He must be feeling really bad now.

252
00:15:46,910 --> 00:15:48,270
Even if I can't see him,

253
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:50,120
there's one way

254
00:15:50,670 --> 00:15:51,510
to reach him.

255
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:52,870
What is it?

256
00:15:53,390 --> 00:15:54,390
Writing letters.

257
00:15:54,670 --> 00:15:55,960
I already wrote one.

258
00:15:56,840 --> 00:15:58,480
But Mom hid it.

259
00:15:59,030 --> 00:16:00,830
Then I'll write him another one.

260
00:16:06,320 --> 00:16:07,200
Sorry,

261
00:16:07,910 --> 00:16:08,750
I'm late.

262
00:16:10,120 --> 00:16:11,760
Just got Yingying home.

263
00:16:11,860 --> 00:16:14,030
This rain just won't stop.

264
00:16:14,910 --> 00:16:15,970
In a couple of days,

265
00:16:16,510 --> 00:16:17,510
I'll file for your release on bail

266
00:16:17,510 --> 00:16:19,030
due to health reasons.

267
00:16:19,960 --> 00:16:21,420
Then you can see Yingying.

268
00:16:22,510 --> 00:16:23,630
She'll be so happy

269
00:16:23,630 --> 00:16:24,840
if she gets to see you.

270
00:16:26,270 --> 00:16:27,840
I hope it's sunny that day.

271
00:16:28,390 --> 00:16:29,550
No rain.

272
00:16:30,600 --> 00:16:31,390
No need.

273
00:16:34,320 --> 00:16:35,000
What?

274
00:16:37,360 --> 00:16:38,440
I said, no need.

275
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:41,930
I want to terminate our agreement.

276
00:16:42,790 --> 00:16:44,100
I'll defend myself.

277
00:16:46,150 --> 00:16:46,870
Why?

278
00:16:48,630 --> 00:16:50,030
Did I do something wrong?

279
00:16:51,100 --> 00:16:52,070
Why?

280
00:16:52,520 --> 00:16:53,960
[No Smoking]

281
00:16:53,960 --> 00:16:54,870
Duan Hongshan.

282
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:57,000
I've been running around

283
00:16:57,320 --> 00:16:58,600
everywhere for your case.

284
00:16:58,600 --> 00:17:00,550
I've done what
I should and shouldn't have.

285
00:17:00,550 --> 00:17:03,480
Now, right before
the finish line, you kick me aside?

286
00:17:03,550 --> 00:17:04,510
Why?

287
00:17:05,069 --> 00:17:05,829
Why?

